title: 05-aparavi-pipeline
text:
This page demonstrates executing an Aparavi DTC pipeline end-to-end using the
[Aparavi SDK](https://pypi.org/project/aparavi-dtc-sdk/). The pipeline ingests
sample documents from Google Drive, parses them, splits the text into chunks,
and returns the processed documents.

title: Pipeline Overview
text:
The pipeline consists of four stages connected in sequence:

1. **Google Drive Source** â€” Pulls documents from the Hackathon sample dataset
2. **Document Parser** â€” Extracts text content from raw files
3. **LangChain Chunker** â€” Splits text using `RecursiveCharacterTextSplitter` with a 512-character window
4. **Response Output** â€” Collects the processed document chunks

title: Pipeline Configuration
text:
The pipeline is defined in `pipelines/pipeline-config.json` and was exported
from the Aparavi platform. Key configuration details:

| Parameter | Value |
|-----------|-------|
| Pipeline ID | `7368b3bc-6c8f-4b85-a97d-a9cb73087108` |
| Source | Google Drive â€” Hackathon dataset |
| Chunk size | 512 characters |
| Splitter | `RecursiveCharacterTextSplitter` |
| Output | Processed document chunks |

title: Tips
text:
- Export a pipeline JSON from the [Aparavi platform](https://core.aparavi.com/)
  and paste it directly into the editor above.
- The JSON must contain a `components` array where each entry defines a pipeline
  stage with `id`, `provider`, `config`, `ui`, and `input` fields.
- Make sure your `.env` file has valid `APARAVI_API_KEY` and `APARAVI_BASE_URL`
  values before executing.

title: Pipeline Playground
text:
Run Aparavi DTC pipelines directly in the browser using your own API key. Enter
your credentials below, edit the pipeline configuration, and click
**Execute Pipeline** to see results.

title: Tips
text:
- Get your API key from the [Aparavi platform](https://core.aparavi.com/).
- The default base URL (`https://eaas.aparavi.com/`) works for most accounts.
  Change it only if your organization uses a different endpoint.
- Export a pipeline JSON from the Aparavi platform and paste it into the editor
  to run your own pipelines.
